{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896355360,"sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","part":{"id":"prt_d7babe13e001hFtrX6sGpbDP4u","messageID":"msg_d7babd269001fiFvTISe42e60W","sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-7673a28634a74e28b3373a56a73d77c8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube 核心模块测试契约 (TDD Manifest)\n2: \n3: 本规范定义了系统各核心组件必须实现的最小测试集。未通过以下测试用例的实现将被判定为“跑偏”。\n4: \n5: ## 1. Workload Manager (Go) - 核心准入测试\n6: - **Func: `CreateSandbox`**\n7:     - **Test-WM-1**: 必须 Mock Kubernetes Client，验证 `sandbox` 资源被正确创建。\n8:     - **Test-WM-2**: 验证 Session 冲突处理（同名 Sandbox 冲突时返回 409 或恢复现有会话）。\n9:     - **Test-WM-3**: 验证 Pod 状态同步逻辑。模拟 Pod 变为 `Running` 状态，验证 API 返回正确的 `Endpoint`。\n10: - **Func: `DeleteSession`**\n11:     - **Test-WM-4**: 验证物理资源的清理。确保调用了 K8s Delete API 且 Redis 记录同步删除。\n12: \n13: ## 2. Router (Go) - 高并发与安全测试\n14: - **Middleware: `AuthMiddleware`**\n15:     - **Test-RT-1**: 构造非法 JWT，验证返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n16:     - **Test-RT-2**: 构造过期 JWT，验证返回 `Token Expired`。\n17: - **Proxy Logic: `HandleProxy`**\n18:     - **Test-RT-3**: 模拟后端超时，验证 Proxy 正确处理 `Gateway Timeout` 且不崩溃。\n19:     - **Test-RT-4**: 验证 Header 透传（Host, X-Forwarded-For 等）。\n20: \n21: ## 3. Session Store (Go) - 强一致性测试\n22: - **Store Interface: `RedisStore` / `ValkeyStore`**\n23:     - **Test-ST-1**: 验证对象序列化与反序列化（SessionInfo -> JSON -> SessionInfo）。\n24:     - **Test-ST-2**: 并发写测试。模拟 100 个并发请求写入同一 Session，验证无 Data Race。\n25: \n26: ## 4. PicoD (Go) - 执行引擎隔离测试\n27: - **Executor: `RunCode`**\n28:     - **Test-PD-1**: 验证资源限制（如 OOM）。模拟大内存分配，验证进程被正确杀掉并返回错误。\n29:     - **Test-PD-2**: 验证 Stdout 分块读取。处理超过 1MB 的输出，验证无缓冲区溢出。\n30: \n31: ## 5. Python SDK & CLI - 兼容性与易用性测试\n32: - **Class: `CodeInterpreterClient`**\n33:     - **Test-SDK-1**: 验证所有 HTTP 状态码映射。404 -> `NotFoundError`, 429 -> `RateLimitError`。\n34:     - **Test-SDK-2**: 验证文件上传协议。构造二进制流，验证 Multipart 封装符合 Router 规范。\n35: - **CLI: `kubectl-agentcube`**\n36:     - **Test-CLI-1**: 验证 `run` 命令的参数解析。测试 `--image`, `--env` 等参数的正确合并。\n37: \n38: ## 物理指标要求\n39: 1.  **测试/代码行数比 (T/C Ratio)**: 必须 > 0.4 (即每 100 行代码至少 40 行测试)。\n40: 2.  **用例完整性**: 每个源文件（`*.go`, `*.py`）必须存在对应的 `*_test.go` 或 `test_*.py`。\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube 核心模块测试契约 (TDD Manifest)\n\n本规范定义了系统各核心组件必须实现的最小测试集。未通过以下测试用例的实现将被判定为“跑偏”。\n\n## 1. Workload Manager (Go) - 核心准入测试\n- **Func: `CreateSandbox`**\n    - **Test-WM-1**: 必须 Mock Kubernetes Client，验证 `sandbox` 资源被正确创建。\n    - **Test-WM-2**: 验证 Session 冲突处理（同名 Sandbox 冲突时返回 409 或恢复现有会话）。\n    - **Test-WM-3**: 验证 Pod 状态同步逻辑。模拟 Pod 变为 `Running` 状态，验证 API 返回正确的 `Endpoint`。\n- **Func: `DeleteSession`**\n    - **Test-WM-4**: 验证物理资源的清理。确保调用了 K8s Delete API 且 Redis 记录同步删除。\n\n## 2. Router (Go) - 高并发与安全测试\n- **Middleware: `AuthMiddleware`**\n    - **Test-RT-1**: 构造非法 JWT，验证返回 `401 Unauthorized`。\n    - **Test-RT-2**: 构造过期 JWT，验证返回 `Token Expired`。\n- **Proxy Logic: `HandleProxy`**\n    - **Test-RT-3**: 模拟后端超时，验证 Proxy 正确处理 `Gateway Timeout` 且不崩溃。\n    - **Test-RT-4**: 验证 Header 透传（Host, X-Forwarded-For 等）。\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md","time":{"start":1775896355348,"end":1775896355359}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896355365,"sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","part":{"id":"prt_d7babdeac001n3oxOt4woz3D23","messageID":"msg_d7babd269001fiFvTISe42e60W","sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4af15416d370458aa1f4859f89f7d935","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design-testing.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design-testing.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # pkg/workloadmanager — Go Unit Testing Design\n2: \n3: ## AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n4: \n5: **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n6: **Language**: Go\n7: **Size**: L\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: This design document outlines the comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module, which provides HTTP API services for creating and managing agent runtime sandboxes, session lifecycle management, and integration with Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\n12: \n13: ## Testing Architecture\n14: \n15: ### Test Organization\n16: \n17: ```\n18: pkg/workloadmanager/\n19: ├── api/\n20: │   ├── types.go\n21: │   ├── response.go\n22: │   ├── response_test.go         # HTTP response utilities tests\n23: │   └── (api_handlers_test.go)   # Future: API handler tests\n24: ├── controller/\n25: │   ├── sandbox.go\n26: │   ├── sandbox_test.go          # Sandbox controller tests\n27: │   └── (reconciler_test.go)     # Future: Reconciler tests\n28: ├── handler/\n29: │   ├── handler.go\n30: │   ├── handler_test.go          # HTTP handler tests\n31: │   ├── sandbox.go\n32: │   └── sandbox_test.go          # Sandbox-specific handler tests\n33: ├── client/\n34: │   ├── k8s_client.go\n35: │   └── k8s_client_test.go       # Kubernetes client tests\n36: ├── config/\n37: │   ├── config.go\n38: │   └── config_test.go           # Configuration tests\n39: ├── middleware/\n40: │   ├── middleware.go\n41: │   └── middleware_test.go       # HTTP middleware tests\n42: ├── gc/\n43: │   ├── collector.go\n44: │   ├── collector_test.go        # GC collector tests\n45: │   ├── policy.go\n46: │   ├── policy_test.go           # GC policy tests\n47: │   ├── scheduler.go\n48: │   ├── scheduler_test.go        # GC scheduler tests\n49: │   ├── metrics.go\n50: │   └── metrics_test.go          # GC metrics tests\n51: ├── types/\n52: │   └── sandbox_types.go\n53: ├── garbage_collector.go\n54: ├── garbage_collector_test.go    # Legacy garbage collector tests\n55: ├── defaults.go\n56: └── design.md                    # This document\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Testing Strategy\n60: \n61: #### Unit Test Levels\n62: \n63: 1. **Component-Level Tests**: Test individual functions and methods in isolation\n64: 2. **Integration-Level Tests**: Test interactions between closely related components\n65: 3. **Behavioral Tests**: Test end-to-end behavior using mocked dependencies\n66: \n67: #### Test Categories\n68: \n69: 1. **Happy Path Tests**: Verify correct behavior with valid inputs\n70: 2. **Error Path Tests**: Verify error handling and edge cases\n71: 3. **Boundary Condition Tests**: Test limits and thresholds\n72: 4. **Concurrency Tests**: Verify thread-safety where applicable\n73: 5. **Performance Tests**: Verify performance characteristics (optional)\n74: \n75: ### Testing Framework\n76: \n77: #### Standard Library + Third-Party Libraries\n78: \n79: ```go\n80: // Testing framework\n81: import \"testing\"\n82: \n83: // Assertion library\n84: import \"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n85: import \"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n86: import \"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n87: \n88: // HTTP testing\n89: import \"net/http/httptest\"\n90: \n91: // Kubernetes fake clients\n92: import \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n93: import \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n94: \n95: // Redis testing\n96: import \"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2\"\n97: ```\n98: \n99: #### Test Helpers\n100: \n101: Common test utilities to be created:\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: // pkg/workloadmanager/testing/fakes.go\n105: package testing\n106: \n107: import (\n108:     \"context\"\n109:     \"testing\"\n110:     \"time\"\n111: \n112:     \"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2\"\n113:     \"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n114:     corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n115:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n116:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1/unstructured\"\n117:     \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n118:     \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic\"\n119:     \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n120:     \"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n121: \n122:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n123:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n124:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n125:     wmClient \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/client\"\n126: )\n127: \n128: // TestFixtures provides common test data and helpers\n129: type TestFixtures struct {\n130:     T           *testing.T\n131:     MiniRedis   *miniredis.Miniredis\n132:     Store       store.Store\n133:     FakeDynamic dynamic.Interface\n134:     FakeK8s     kubernetes.Interface\n135:     MockStore   *MockStore\n136:     MockK8s     *MockK8sClient\n137: }\n138: \n139: // NewTestFixtures creates a new test fixtures setup\n140: func NewTestFixtures(t *testing.T) *TestFixtures {\n141:     mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n142:     redisStore, err := store.NewValkeyStore(mr.Addr(), \"\", 0)\n143:     require.NoError(t, err)\n144: \n145:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n146:     v1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n147: \n148:     return &TestFixtures{\n149:         T:           t,\n150:         MiniRedis:   mr,\n151:         Store:       redisStore,\n152:         FakeDynamic: fake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme),\n153:         FakeK8s:     fake.NewSimpleClientset(),\n154:         MockStore:   NewMockStore(),\n155:         MockK8s:     NewMockK8sClient(),\n156:     }\n157: }\n158: \n159: // Cleanup performs cleanup operations\n160: func (tf *TestFixtures) Cleanup() {\n161:     tf.Store.Close()\n162:     tf.MiniRedis.Close()\n163: }\n164: \n165: // Helper functions for creating test objects\n166: func CreateTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace string) *unstructured.Unstructured {\n167:     return &unstructured.Unstructured{\n168:         Object: map[string]interface{}{\n169:             \"apiVersion\": \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\",\n170:             \"kind\":       \"AgentRuntime\",\n171:             \"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n172:                 \"name\":      name,\n173:                 \"namespace\": namespace,\n174:             },\n175:             \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n176:                 \"sessionTimeout\":     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n177:                 \"maxSessionDuration\": &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n178:                 \"podTemplate\": map[string]interface{}{\n179:                     \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n180:                         \"containers\": []interface{}{\n181:                             map[string]interface{}{\n182:                                 \"name\":  \"agent\",\n183:                                 \"image\": \"python:3.11-slim\",\n184:                             },\n185:                         },\n186:                     },\n187:                 },\n188:                 \"ports\": []interface{}{\n189:                     map[string]interface{}{\n190:                         \"port\":     int64(8080),\n191:                         \"protocol\": \"HTTP\",\n192:                     },\n193:                 },\n194:             },\n195:         },\n196:     }\n197: }\n198: \n199: func CreateTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace string) *unstructured.Unstructured {\n200:     return &unstructured.Unstructured{\n201:         Object: map[string]interface{}{\n202:             \"apiVersion\": \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\",\n203:             \"kind\":       \"CodeInterpreter\",\n204:             \"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n205:                 \"name\":      name,\n206:                 \"namespace\": namespace,\n207:             },\n208:             \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n209:                 \"template\": map[string]interface{}{\n210:                     \"image\": \"python:3.11-slim\",\n211:                 },\n212:             },\n213:         },\n214:     }\n215: }\n216: \n217: func CreateTestSandbox(name, namespace, sessionID string) *unstructured.Unstructured {\n218:     return &unstructured.Unstructured{\n219:         Object: map[string]interface{}{\n220:             \"apiVersion\": \"agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1\",\n221:             \"kind\":       \"Sandbox\",\n222:             \"metadata\": map[string]interface{}{\n223:                 \"name\":      name,\n224:                 \"namespace\": namespace,\n225:                 \"labels\": map[string]interface{}{\n226:                     \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\": sessionID,\n227:                 },\n228:             },\n229:             \"spec\": map[string]interface{}{\n230:                 \"replicas\": int64(1),\n231:             },\n232:         },\n233:     }\n234: }\n235: \n236: func CreateTestSandboxInfo(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n237:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n238:         SessionID:    sessionID,\n239:         SandboxID:    \"sandbox-\" + sessionID,\n240:         SandboxName:  \"test-sandbox\",\n241:         WorkloadName: \"test-workload\",\n242:         Namespace:    \"default\",\n243:         Kind:         \"AgentRuntime\",\n244:         Status:       \"running\",\n245:         CreatedAt:    time.Now(),\n246:         ExpiresAt:    time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour),\n247:         PodIP:        \"10.244.1.5\",\n248:         EntryPoints: []types.SandboxEntryPoint{\n249:             {\n250:                 Protocol: \"HTTP\",\n251:                 Endpoint: \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n252:                 Path:     \"/\",\n253:             },\n254:         },\n255:         LastActivityAt: time.Now(),\n256:     }\n257: }\n258: ```\n259: \n260: ## Component-Specific Testing\n261: \n262: ### 1. API Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/api/`)\n263: \n264: #### Test Coverage\n265: \n266: **`response_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n267: - ✅ Error response formatting\n268: - ✅ JSON response formatting\n269: - ✅ Error code formatting\n270: \n271: **Future tests needed:**\n272: - `types_test.go`: Type validation and serialization\n273: \n274: #### Example Test Pattern\n275: \n276: ```go\n277: func TestCreateSandboxRequest_Validation(t *testing.T) {\n278:     tests := []struct {\n279:         name    string\n280:         req     api.CreateSandboxRequest\n281:         wantErr bool\n282:     }{\n283:         {\n284:             name: \"valid request\",\n285:             req: api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n286:                 Kind:      \"AgentRuntime\",\n287:                 Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n288:                 Namespace: \"default\",\n289:             },\n290:             wantErr: false,\n291:         },\n292:         {\n293:             name: \"missing kind\",\n294:             req: api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n295:                 Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n296:                 Namespace: \"default\",\n297:             },\n298:             wantErr: true,\n299:         },\n300:         {\n301:             name: \"invalid kind\",\n302:             req: api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n303:                 Kind:      \"InvalidKind\",\n304:                 Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n305:                 Namespace: \"default\",\n306:             },\n307:             wantErr: true,\n308:         },\n309:     }\n310: \n311:     for _, tt := range tests {\n312:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n313:             err := tt.req.Validate()\n314:             if (err != nil) != tt.wantErr {\n315:                 t.Errorf(\"CreateSandboxRequest.Validate() error = %v, wantErr %v\", err, tt.wantErr)\n316:             }\n317:         })\n318:     }\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### 2. Controller Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/controller/`)\n323: \n324: #### Test Coverage\n325: \n326: **`sandbox_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n327: - ✅ Create AgentRuntime sandbox\n328: - ✅ Create CodeInterpreter sandbox\n329: - ✅ Get session\n330: - ✅ Delete session\n331: - ✅ Build sandbox CRs\n332: - ✅ Build entry points\n333: - ✅ Generate sandbox names\n334: - ✅ Error handling scenarios\n335: \n336: #### Test Patterns\n337: \n338: ```go\n339: func TestSandboxController_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n340:     fixtures := NewTestFixtures(t)\n341:     defer fixtures.Cleanup()\n342: \n343:     t.Run(\"successfully creates sandbox\", func(t *testing.T) {\n344:         ctx := context.Background()\n345:         controller := NewSandboxController(fixtures.MockK8s, fixtures.Store)\n346: \n347:         req := &api.CreateSandboxRequest{\n348:             Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n349:             Namespace: \"default\",\n350:         }\n351: \n352:         agentRuntime := CreateTestAgentRuntime(\"test-runtime\", \"default\")\n353:         sandboxCR := CreateTestSandbox(\"test-runtime-abc123\", \"default\", \"session-123\")\n354: \n355:         fixtures.MockK8s.On(\"GetAgentRuntime\", mock.Anything, \"default\", \"test-runtime\").Return(agentRuntime, nil)\n356:         fixtures.MockK8s.On(\"CreateSandbox\", ctx, \"default\", mock.AnythingOfType(\"*unstructured.Unstructured\")).Return(sandboxCR, nil)\n357:         fixtures.MockK8s.On(\"GetPodIP\", mock.Anything, mock.Anything, \"default\", mock.Anything).Return(\"10.244.1.5\", nil)\n358: \n359:         resp, err := controller.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(ctx, req)\n360: \n361:         require.NoError(t, err)\n362:         require.NotNil(t, resp)\n363:         assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SessionID)\n364:         assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SandboxID)\n365:         assert.Equal(t, \"HTTP\", resp.EntryPoints[0].Protocol)\n366: \n367:         fixtures.MockK8s.AssertExpectations(t)\n368:     })\n369: }\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### 3. Handler Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/handler/`)\n373: \n374: #### Test Coverage\n375: \n376: **`handler_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n377: - ✅ Create AgentRuntime sandbox handler\n378: - ✅ Create CodeInterpreter sandbox handler\n379: - ✅ Get session handler\n380: - ✅ Delete session handler\n381: - ✅ Health check handler\n382: - ✅ Request body validation\n383: - ✅ Error responses\n384: \n385: **`sandbox_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n386: - ✅ Handle delete sandbox\n387: - ✅ Handle SandboxClaim deletion\n388: - ✅ Error handling\n389: \n390: #### Test Patterns\n391: \n392: ```go\n393: func TestHandler_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n394:     gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)\n395:     mockCtrl := new(MockSandboxController)\n396:     router := setupRouter(mockCtrl)\n397: \n398:     t.Run(\"successfully creates sandbox\", func(t *testing.T) {\n399:         expectedResp := &api.CreateSandboxResponse{\n400:             SessionID:   \"session-123\",\n401:             SandboxID:   \"sandbox-123\",\n402:             SandboxName: \"test-runtime-abc123\",\n403:             EntryPoints: []api.EntryPoint{\n404:                 {\n405:                     Protocol: \"HTTP\",\n406:                     Endpoint: \"10.244.1.5:8080\",\n407:                     Port:     8080,\n408:                 },\n409:             },\n410:             CreatedAt: time.Now().Format(time.RFC3339),\n411:             ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(8 * time.Hour).Format(time.RFC3339),\n412:         }\n413: \n414:         mockCtrl.On(\"CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox\", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(expectedResp, nil)\n415: \n416:         reqBody := map[string]interface{}{\n417:             \"kind\":      \"AgentRuntime\",\n418:             \"name\":      \"test-runtime\",\n419:             \"namespace\": \"default\",\n420:         }\n421:         body, _ := json.Marshal(reqBody)\n422: \n423:         req := httptest.NewRequest(\"POST\", \"/v1/agent-runtime\", bytes.NewBuffer(body))\n424:         req.Header.Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n425:         w := httptest.NewRecorder()\n426: \n427:         router.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n428: \n429:         assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n430: \n431:         var resp api.CreateSandboxResponse\n432:         err := json.Unmarshal(w.Body.Bytes(), &resp)\n433:         require.NoError(t, err)\n434:         assert.Equal(t, \"session-123\", resp.SessionID)\n435: \n436:         mockCtrl.AssertExpectations(t)\n437:     })\n438: }\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### 4. Client Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/client/`)\n442: \n443: #### Test Coverage\n444: \n445: **`k8s_client_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n446: - ✅ Get AgentRuntime\n447: - ✅ Get CodeInterpreter\n448: - ✅ Create sandbox\n449: - ✅ Get sandbox\n450: - ✅ Delete sandbox\n451: - ✅ Error handling (not found scenarios)\n452: \n453: #### Test Patterns\n454: \n455: ```go\n456: func TestK8sClient_GetAgentRuntime(t *testing.T) {\n457:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n458:     err := v1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)\n459:     require.NoError(t, err)\n460: \n461:     agentRuntime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n462:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n463:             Name:      \"test-runtime\",\n464:             Namespace: \"default\",\n465:         },\n466:         Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n467:             SessionTimeout:     &metav1.Duration{Duration: 15 * time.Minute},\n468:             MaxSessionDuration: &metav1.Duration{Duration: 8 * time.Hour},\n469:         },\n470:     }\n471: \n472:     agentRuntimeUnstructured, err := runtime.DefaultUnstructuredConverter.ToUnstructured(agentRuntime)\n473:     require.NoError(t, err)\n474: \n475:     agentRuntimeObj := &unstructured.Unstructured{Object: agentRuntimeUnstructured}\n476:     agentRuntimeObj.SetAPIVersion(\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\")\n477:     agentRuntimeObj.SetKind(\"AgentRuntime\")\n478: \n479:     dynamicClient := fake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(scheme)\n480:     gvr := schema.GroupVersionResource{\n481:         Group:    \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\",\n482:         Version:  \"v1alpha1\",\n483:         Resource: \"agentruntimes\",\n484:     }\n485: \n486:     _, err = dynamicClient.Resource(gvr).Namespace(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), agentRuntimeObj, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n487:     require.NoError(t, err)\n488: \n489:     k8sClient := &wmClient.K8sClient{\n490:         dynamic:  dynamicClient,\n491:         gvrAgent: gvr,\n492:     }\n493: \n494:     t.Run(\"successfully gets agent runtime\", func(t *testing.T) {\n495:         result, err := k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(context.Background(), \"default\", \"test-runtime\")\n496: \n497:         require.NoError(t, err)\n498:         require.NotNil(t, result)\n499:         assert.Equal(t, \"test-runtime\", result.GetName())\n500:     })\n501: \n502:     t.Run(\"agent runtime not found\", func(t *testing.T) {\n503:         _, err := k8sClient.GetAgentRuntime(context.Background(), \"default\", \"nonexistent\")\n504: \n505:         require.Error(t, err)\n506:         assert.True(t, apierrors.IsNotFound(err))\n507:     })\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### 5. GC Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/gc/`)\n512: \n513: #### Test Coverage\n514: \n515: **`collector_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n516: - ✅ NewGCCollector initialization\n517: - ✅ Collect with no candidates\n518: - ✅ Collect expired sandbox\n519: - ✅ Collect idle sandbox\n520: - ✅ Dry run mode\n521: - ✅ Session not found handling\n522: - ✅ SandboxClaim deletion\n523: \n524: **`policy_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n525: - ✅ DefaultGCConfig\n526: - ✅ NewGCPolicy initialization\n527: - ✅ Label selector validation\n528: - ✅ Namespace filtering\n529: - ✅ Expiration detection\n530: - ✅ Idle detection\n531: - ✅ Orphan detection\n532: - ✅ ShouldGC logic\n533: \n534: **`scheduler_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n535: - ✅ NewGCScheduler initialization\n536: - ✅ RunOnce execution\n537: - ✅ Start/Stop lifecycle\n538: - ✅ Config updates\n539: - ✅ Error handling\n540: \n541: **`metrics_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n542: - ✅ Metrics initialization\n543: - ✅ Record operations\n544: - ✅ Concurrent access\n545: \n546: #### Test Patterns\n547: \n548: ```go\n549: func TestGCCollector_Collect_ExpiredSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n550:     mockStore := &mockStore{}\n551:     scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n552: \n553:     scheme.AddKnownTypes(schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"agents.x-k8s.io\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"},\n554:         &unstructured.Unstructured{},\n555:         &unstructured.UnstructuredList{},\n556:     )\n557: \n558:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleDynamicClientWithCustomListKinds(scheme, map[schema.GroupVersionResource]string{\n559:         SandboxGVR:       \"SandboxList\",\n560:         SandboxClaimGVR:  \"SandboxClaimList\",\n561:     })\n562: \n563:     sessionID := \"test-session\"\n564:     sandboxInfo := &types.SandboxInfo{\n565:         SessionID:        sessionID,\n566:         SandboxID:        \"test-sandbox\",\n567:         SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n568:         Kind:             \"Sandbox\",\n569:         LastActivityAt:   time.Now(),\n570:         ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(1 * time.Hour),\n571:     }\n572: \n573:     mockStore.On(\"GetSandbox\", mock.Anything, sessionID).Return(sandboxInfo, nil)\n574:     mockStore.On(\"DeleteSandboxBySessionID\", mock.Anything, sessionID).Return(nil)\n575: \n576:     sandbox := buildTestSandbox(\"test-sandbox\", \"default\", sessionID, 24*time.Hour)\n577:     fakeClient.Resource(SandboxGVR).Namespace(\"default\").Create(context.Background(), sandbox, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n578: \n579:     config := &GCConfig{\n580:         MaxAge:        1 * time.Hour,\n581:         IdleTimeout:   15 * time.Minute,\n582:         DryRun:        false,\n583:         Namespaces:    []string{},\n584:         LabelSelector: \"\",\n585:     }\n586:     policy, _ := NewGCPolicy(config)\n587:     metrics := NewGCMetrics()\n588: \n589:     collector := NewGCCollector(fakeClient, mockStore, config, policy, metrics)\n590: \n591:     ctx := context.Background()\n592:     result, err := collector.Collect(ctx)\n593: \n594:     assert.NoError(t, err)\n595:     assert.NotNil(t, result)\n596:     assert.Equal(t, 1, result.Scanned)\n597:     assert.Equal(t, 1, result.Candidates)\n598:     assert.Equal(t, 1, result.Deleted)\n599:     assert.Equal(t, 0, result.Errors)\n600: \n601:     mockStore.AssertExpectations(t)\n602: }\n603: ```\n604: \n605: ### 6. Config Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/config/`)\n606: \n607: #### Test Coverage\n608: \n609: **`config_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n610: - ✅ DefaultConfig values\n611: - ✅ All configuration fields\n612: \n613: ### 7. Middleware Layer (`pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`)\n614: \n615: #### Test Coverage\n616: \n617: **`middleware_test.go`** (Already implemented):\n618: - ✅ Recovery middleware panic handling\n619: - ✅ CORS headers\n620: - ✅ Logging middleware\n621: \n622: ## Mock Objects\n623: \n624: ### Mock Store\n625: \n626: ```go\n627: // pkg/workloadmanager/testing/mocks.go\n628: package testing\n629: \n630: import (\n631:     \"context\"\n632:     \"testing\"\n633:     \"time\"\n634: \n635:     \"github.com/stretchr/testify/mock\"\n636: \n637:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n638:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store\"\n639: )\n640: \n641: type MockStore struct {\n642:     mock.Mock\n643: }\n644: \n645: func (m *MockStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error {\n646:     args := m.Called(ctx)\n647:     return args.Error(0)\n648: }\n649: \n650: func (m *MockStore) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n651:     args := m.Called(ctx, sessionID)\n652:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n653:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n654:     }\n655:     return args.Get(0).(*types.SandboxInfo), args.Error(1)\n656: }\n657: \n658: func (m *MockStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n659:     args := m.Called(ctx, sessionID, info)\n660:     return args.Error(0)\n661: }\n662: \n663: func (m *MockStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n664:     args := m.Called(ctx, sessionID, info)\n665:     return args.Error(0)\n666: }\n667: \n668: func (m *MockStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error {\n669:     args := m.Called(ctx, sessionID)\n670:     return args.Error(0)\n671: }\n672: \n673: func (m *MockStore) ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) (map[string]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n674:     args := m.Called(ctx)\n675:     return args.Get(0).(map[string]*types.SandboxInfo), args.Error(1)\n676: }\n677: \n678: func (m *MockStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n679:     args := m.Called(ctx, sessionID, at)\n680:     return args.Error(0)\n681: }\n682: \n683: func (m *MockStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n684:     args := m.Called(ctx, before, limit)\n685:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n686:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n687:     }\n688:     return args.Get(0).([]*types.SandboxInfo), args.Error(1)\n689: }\n690: \n691: func (m *MockStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n692:     args := m.Called(ctx, before, limit)\n693:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n694:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n695:     }\n696:     return args.Get(0).([]*types.SandboxInfo), args.Error(1)\n697: }\n698: \n699: func (m *MockStore) Close() error {\n700:     args := m.Called()\n701:     return args.Error(0)\n702: }\n703: ```\n704: \n705: ### Mock K8s Client\n706: \n707: ```go\n708: type MockK8sClient struct {\n709:     mock.Mock\n710: }\n711: \n712: func (m *MockK8sClient) GetAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n713:     args := m.Called(ctx, namespace, name)\n714:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n715:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n716:     }\n717:     return args.Get(0).(*unstructured.Unstructured), args.Error(1)\n718: }\n719: \n720: func (m *MockK8sClient) GetCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n721:     args := m.Called(ctx, namespace, name)\n722:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n723:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n724:     }\n725:     return args.Get(0).(*unstructured.Unstructured), args.Error(1)\n726: }\n727: \n728: func (m *MockK8sClient) CreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace string, sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n729:     args := m.Called(ctx, namespace, sandbox)\n730:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n731:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n732:     }\n733:     return args.Get(0).(*unstructured.Unstructured), args.Error(1)\n734: }\n735: \n736: func (m *MockK8sClient) GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*unstructured.Unstructured, error) {\n737:     args := m.Called(ctx, namespace, name)\n738:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n739:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n740:     }\n741:     return args.Get(0).(*unstructured.Unstructured), args.Error(1)\n742: }\n743: \n744: func (m *MockK8sClient) DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n745:     args := m.Called(ctx, namespace, name)\n746:     return args.Error(0)\n747: }\n748: \n749: func (m *MockK8sClient) GetPodIP(ctx context.Context, sandboxName, namespace string, sandbox *unstructured.Unstructured) (string, error) {\n750:     args := m.Called(ctx, sandboxName, namespace, sandbox)\n751:     return args.String(0), args.Error(1)\n752: }\n753: \n754: func (m *MockK8sClient) GetSecret(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) (*corev1.Secret, error) {\n755:     args := m.Called(ctx, namespace, name)\n756:     if args.Get(0) == nil {\n757:         return nil, args.Error(1)\n758:     }\n759:     return args.Get(0).(*corev1.Secret), args.Error(1)\n760: }\n761: ```\n762: \n763: ## Test Execution\n764: \n765: ### Running All Tests\n766: \n767: ```bash\n768: # Run all tests in workloadmanager\n769: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -v\n770: \n771: # Run tests with race detection\n772: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -race -v\n773: \n774: # Run tests with coverage\n775: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... -cover -coverprofile=coverage.out\n776: \n777: # Run specific test\n778: go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller -run TestSandboxController_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox -v\n779: ```\n780: \n781: ### Coverage Goals\n782: \n783: | Component | Target Coverage | Current Status |\n784: |-----------|----------------|----------------|\n785: | API Layer | 80%+ | ✅ 85% |\n786: | Controller Layer | 85%+ | ✅ 90% |\n787: | Handler Layer | 85%+ | ✅ 88% |\n788: | Client Layer | 80%+ | ✅ 85% |\n789: | Config Layer | 90%+ | ✅ 95% |\n790: | Middleware Layer | 85%+ | ✅ 90% |\n791: | GC Layer | 85%+ | ✅ 92% |\n792: | **Overall** | **85%+** | ✅ **88%** |\n793: \n794: ## CI/CD Integration\n795: \n796: ### GitHub Actions Workflow\n797: \n798: ```yaml\n799: # .github/workflows/workloadmanager-tests.yml\n800: name: WorkloadManager Tests\n801: \n802: on:\n803:   push:\n804:     paths:\n805:       - 'pkg/workloadmanager/**'\n806:       - 'pkg/common/**'\n807:       - 'pkg/store/**'\n808:       - 'pkg/apis/runtime/**'\n809:   pull_request:\n810:     paths:\n811:       - 'pkg/workloadmanager/**'\n812:       - 'pkg/common/**'\n813:       - 'pkg/store/**'\n814:       - 'pkg/apis/runtime/**'\n815: \n816: jobs:\n817:   test:\n818:     name: Unit Tests\n819:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n820: \n821:     steps:\n822:       - name: Checkout code\n823:         uses: actions/checkout@v3\n824: \n825:       - name: Set up Go\n826:         uses: actions/setup-go@v4\n827:         with:\n828:           go-version: '1.24'\n829: \n830:       - name: Download dependencies\n831:         run: go mod download\n832: \n833:       - name: Run tests\n834:         run: |\n835:           go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/... \\\n836:             -v \\\n837:             -race \\\n838:             -coverprofile=coverage.out \\\n839:             -covermode=atomic\n840: \n841:       - name: Generate coverage report\n842:         run: go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n843: \n844:       - name: Upload coverage\n845:         uses: codecov/codecov-action@v3\n846:         with:\n847:           files: ./coverage.out\n848:           flags: workloadmanager\n849: \n850:   lint:\n851:     name: Lint\n852:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n853: \n854:     steps:\n855:       - name: Checkout code\n856:         uses: actions/checkout@v3\n857: \n858:       - name: Set up Go\n859:         uses: actions/setup-go@v4\n860:         with:\n861:           go-version: '1.24'\n862: \n863:       - name: Run golangci-lint\n864:         uses: golangci/golangci-lint-action@v3\n865:         with:\n866:           version: latest\n867:           working-directory: pkg/workloadmanager\n868: ```\n869: \n870: ### Pre-commit Hooks\n871: \n872: ```yaml\n873: # .pre-commit-config.yaml\n874: repos:\n875:   - repo: local\n876:     hooks:\n877:       - id: go-test-workloadmanager\n878:         name: Go test workloadmanager\n879:         entry: bash -c 'cd pkg/workloadmanager && go test ./... -short'\n880:         language: system\n881:         pass_filenames: false\n882: \n883:       - id: go-lint-workloadmanager\n884:         name: Go lint workloadmanager\n885:         entry: bash -c 'golangci-lint run pkg/workloadmanager/...'\n886:         language: system\n887:         pass_filenames: false\n888: ```\n889: \n890: ## Best Practices\n891: \n892: ### Test Naming Conventions\n893: \n894: ```go\n895: // Function being tested\n896: func Test<Component>_<Function>(t *testing.T)\n897: \n898: // Specific scenario\n899: func Test<Component>_<Function>_<Scenario>(t *testing.T)\n900: \n901: // Example\n902: func TestSandboxController_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(t *testing.T)\n903: func TestSandboxController_CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox_NotFound(t *testing.T)\n904: ```\n905: \n906: ### Table-Driven Tests\n907: \n908: ```go\n909: func TestFunction(t *testing.T) {\n910:     tests := []struct {\n911:         name    string\n912:         input   InputType\n913:         want    OutputType\n914:         wantErr bool\n915:         errType error\n916:     }{\n917:         {\n918:             name:    \"valid input\",\n919:             input:   validInput,\n920:             want:    expectedOutput,\n921:             wantErr: false,\n922:         },\n923:         {\n924:             name:    \"invalid input\",\n925:             input:   invalidInput,\n926:             want:    nil,\n927:             wantErr: true,\n928:             errType: ErrInvalidInput,\n929:         },\n930:     }\n931: \n932:     for _, tt := range tests {\n933:         t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n934:             got, err := Function(tt.input)\n935: \n936:             if tt.wantErr {\n937:                 require.Error(t, err)\n938:                 if tt.errType != nil {\n939:                     assert.ErrorIs(t, err, tt.errType)\n940:                 }\n941:                 return\n942:             }\n943: \n944:             require.NoError(t, err)\n945:             assert.Equal(t, tt.want, got)\n946:         })\n947:     }\n948: }\n949: ```\n950: \n951: ### Test Cleanup\n952: \n953: ```go\n954: func TestFunction(t *testing.T) {\n955:     // Setup\n956:     fixtures := NewTestFixtures(t)\n957:     defer fixtures.Cleanup()\n958: \n959:     // Test code\n960:     // ...\n961: }\n962: ```\n963: \n964: ### Assertions\n965: \n966: ```go\n967: // Use require for fatal assertions (test continues)\n968: require.NoError(t, err)\n969: require.NotNil(t, result)\n970: \n971: // Use assert for non-fatal assertions (test continues)\n972: assert.Equal(t, expected, actual)\n973: assert.Contains(t, str, substring)\n974: assert.True(t, condition)\n975: ```\n976: \n977: ## Performance Considerations\n978: \n979: ### Test Isolation\n980: \n981: - Each test should be independent\n982: - Use table-driven tests for similar scenarios\n983: - Clean up resources in defer statements\n984: \n985: ### Concurrent Testing\n986: \n987: ```go\n988: func TestConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T) {\n989:     var wg sync.WaitGroup\n990:     for i := 0; i < 100; i++ {\n991:         wg.Add(1)\n992:         go func() {\n993:             defer wg.Done()\n994:             // Test code\n995:         }()\n996:     }\n997:     wg.Wait()\n998: }\n999: ```\n1000: \n1001: ### Benchmark Tests (Optional)\n1002: \n1003: ```go\n1004: func BenchmarkFunction(b *testing.B) {\n1005:     for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n1006:         Function(testInput)\n1007:     }\n1008: }\n1009: ```\n1010: \n1011: ## Documentation\n1012: \n1013: ### Test Documentation\n1014: \n1015: Each test file should include:\n1016: 1. Purpose of the tests\n1017: 2. Test data sources\n1018: 3. Mock behavior documentation\n1019: \n1020: ```go\n1021: // TestSandboxController provides unit tests for the SandboxController.\n1022: //\n1023: // The tests cover:\n1024: // - Sandbox creation for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\n1025: // - Session retrieval and deletion\n1026: // - Error handling and edge cases\n1027: //\n1028: // Mock objects are used to isolate the controller from external dependencies\n1029: // such as Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\n1030: package controller_test\n1031: ```\n1032: \n1033: ### Comments in Tests\n1034: \n1035: ```go\n1036: t.Run(\"successfully creates sandbox\", func(t *testing.T) {\n1037:     // Arrange\n1038:     ctx := context.Background()\n1039:     controller := NewSandboxController(fixtures.MockK8s, fixtures.Store)\n1040:     req := &api.CreateSandboxRequest{Name: \"test-runtime\", Namespace: \"default\"}\n1041: \n1042:     // Act\n1043:     resp, err := controller.CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox(ctx, req)\n1044: \n1045:     // Assert\n1046:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1047:     require.NotNil(t, resp)\n1048:     assert.NotEmpty(t, resp.SessionID)\n1049: })\n1050: ```\n1051: \n1052: ## Future Enhancements\n1053: \n1054: ### Potential Areas for Additional Testing\n1055: \n1056: 1. **Integration Tests**: Full-stack tests with real Kubernetes cluster (kind/minikube)\n1057: 2. **End-to-End Tests**: Tests covering complete user workflows\n1058: 3. **Load Tests**: Performance tests under high load\n1059: 4. **Fuzz Testing**: Property-based testing for input validation\n1060: 5. **Contract Tests**: API contract verification\n1061: \n1062: ### Test Infrastructure Improvements\n1063: \n1064: 1. **Test Container Management**: Better setup/teardown for external dependencies\n1065: 2. **Golden File Testing**: For complex output validation\n1066: 3. **Test Data Generation**: Programmatic test data creation\n1067: 4. **Coverage Visualization**: Better coverage reporting\n1068: \n1069: ## Conclusion\n1070: \n1071: The `pkg/workloadmanager` module has comprehensive unit test coverage across all major components. The testing strategy emphasizes:\n1072: \n1073: 1. **Isolation**: Using mocks to test components independently\n1074: 2. **Clarity**: Table-driven tests with descriptive names\n1075: 3. **Reliability**: Proper cleanup and resource management\n1076: 4. **Maintainability**: Shared test fixtures and helpers\n1077: \n1078: The existing test suite achieves 88% overall coverage and follows Go testing best practices. Future enhancements can focus on integration testing and more complex scenario coverage.\n\n(End of file - total 1078 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# pkg/workloadmanager — Go Unit Testing Design\n\n## AR-038 — Go Unit Testing (workloadmanager)\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: L\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the comprehensive unit testing strategy for the `pkg/workloadmanager` module, which provides HTTP API services for creating and managing agent runtime sandboxes, session lifecycle management, and integration with Kubernetes API and Redis storage.\n\n## Testing Architecture\n\n### Test Organization\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── api/\n│   ├── types.go","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design-testing.md","time":{"start":1775896355344,"end":1775896355363}}}}
