{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775896384353,"sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","part":{"id":"prt_d7bac536000179A65iS102VrrN","messageID":"msg_d7bac377e001foSSTNUe5U5ECd","sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896485566,"sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","part":{"id":"prt_d7baddd75001zF3AsDgvLPTSeS","messageID":"msg_d7bac377e001foSSTNUe5U5ECd","sessionID":"ses_2845470bcffeOiOnx857OZvVDi","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e010358a425f4f588988ee97adbe0aa2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-041: E2E Integration Tests — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the technical implementation of comprehensive end-to-end (E2E) integration tests for the AgentCube project. The E2E test suite validates the complete system behavior by deploying a real or simulated Kubernetes environment, creating AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, and verifying end-to-end workflows including session creation, invocation, routing, and lifecycle management.\n\n**Module:** `test/e2e`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Source Root:** `/test/e2e/`  \n**Size:** L  \n**Dependencies:** client-go, kind/minikube/k3s, Ginkgo/Gomega\n\n## Architecture\n\n### E2E Test Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    E2E Test Framework                       │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │           Test Execution Layer                        │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │  Ginkgo Test Suite                             │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Test Organization (Describe/Context/It)     │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Lifecycle Hooks (BeforeSuite/AfterSuite)   │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Parallel Execution Support                 │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                           │                                  │\n│                           ▼                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │           Kubernetes Environment Layer                │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │  Environment Setup (kind/minikube/k3s)         │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Cluster Provisioning                       │  │  │\n│  │  │  • AgentCube Deployment                        │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Resource Cleanup                           │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │  Environment Interface                        │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Kubeconfig Management                      │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Client Configuration                       │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Namespace Management                       │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                           │                                  │\n│                           ▼                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │           Test Helpers & Utilities Layer             │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │  Resource Assertions                          │  │  │\n│  │  │  • CRD Creation Verification                  │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Pod Status Checking                        │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Service Endpoint Verification              │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │  HTTP Client Utilities                        │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Request/Response Validation                │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Timeout Handling                           │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Retry Logic                               │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │  Data Generators                              │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Sample AgentRuntime Specs                  │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Sample CodeInterpreter Specs               │  │  │\n│  │  │  • Test Payload Generators                    │  │  │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                           │                                  │\n│                           ▼                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│           System Under Test (SUT)                         │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  AgentRuntime CRDs  │  CodeInterpreter CRDs          │  │\n│  │  workload-manager   │  router                        │  │\n│  │  session-store      │  picod                         │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Test Categories\n\n```\ntest/e2e/\n├── agentruntime/                    # AgentRuntime E2E tests\n│   ├── agentruntime_suite_test.go  # Main test suite\n│   ├── creation_test.go            # Creation workflow tests\n│   ├── invocation_test.go          # Invocation workflow tests\n│   ├── lifecycle_test.go           # Lifecycle management tests\n│   └── error_handling_test.go      # Error scenario tests\n├── codeinterpreter/                # CodeInterpreter E2E tests\n│   ├── codeinterpreter_suite_test.go\n│   ├── creation_test.go\n│   ├── execution_test.go\n│   ├── file_operations_test.go\n│   └── error_handling_test.go\n├── integration/                    # Cross-component tests\n│   ├── workflow_test.go            # End-to-end workflow tests\n│   ├── routing_test.go             # Routing integration tests\n│   ├── session_management_test.go  # Session lifecycle tests\n│   └── scalability_test.go         # Load and stress tests\n├── framework/                      # Test framework code\n│   ├── framework.go                # Core framework setup\n│   ├── helpers.go                  # Common test helpers\n│   ├── assertions.go               # Custom assertions\n│   └── fixtures.go                 # Test fixtures\n└── manifests/                      # Test manifests\n    ├── agentruntimes/              # AgentRuntime test manifests\n    ├── codeinterpreters/           # CodeInterpreter test manifests\n    └── deployments/                # Deployment configurations\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Framework Configuration\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/framework/framework.go`\n\n```go\n// TestFramework provides the core E2E test framework\ntype TestFramework struct {\n    // Client configuration\n    config      *rest.Config\n    clientset   *kubernetes.Clientset\n    agentClient *agentclient.Clientset\n    \n    // Test environment\n    namespace   string\n    clusterName string\n    \n    // HTTP client for service endpoints\n    httpClient *http.Client\n    \n    // Test state\n    cleanup     []func() error\n}\n\n// FrameworkOptions provides configuration for TestFramework\ntype FrameworkOptions struct {\n    // Namespace is the test namespace (default: e2e-test-<random>)\n    Namespace string\n    \n    // ClusterName identifies the cluster (for multi-cluster tests)\n    ClusterName string\n    \n    // Timeout is the default timeout for operations (default: 5m)\n    Timeout time.Duration\n    \n    // PollInterval is the default poll interval (default: 1s)\n    PollInterval time.Duration\n    \n    // SkipCleanup skips resource cleanup after tests (default: false)\n    SkipCleanup bool\n}\n\n// NewDefaultFramework creates a framework with default options\nfunc NewDefaultFramework(name string) *TestFramework {\n    return NewFramework(name, FrameworkOptions{})\n}\n\n// NewFramework creates a test framework with custom options\nfunc NewFramework(name string, opts FrameworkOptions) *TestFramework\n```\n\n### Test Helpers\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/framework/helpers.go`\n\n```go\n// AgentRuntimeHelper provides utilities for AgentRuntime E2E tests\ntype AgentRuntimeHelper struct {\n    framework *TestFramework\n}\n\n// NewAgentRuntimeHelper creates a new AgentRuntime helper\nfunc NewAgentRuntimeHelper(f *TestFramework) *AgentRuntimeHelper\n\n// CreateAgentRuntime creates an AgentRuntime resource\nfunc (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) CreateAgentRuntime(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    agent *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime,\n) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\n// GetAgentRuntime retrieves an AgentRuntime resource\nfunc (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) GetAgentRuntime(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    name string,\n) (*v1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n\n// WaitForAgentRuntimeReady waits for AgentRuntime to be ready\nfunc (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    name string,\n    timeout time.Duration,\n) error\n\n// CreateSession creates a session via workload-manager API\nfunc (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) CreateSession(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    req *api.CreateSandboxRequest,\n) (*api.CreateSandboxResponse, error)\n\n// InvokeSession invokes a session via router\nfunc (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) InvokeSession(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    sessionID string,\n    payload []byte,\n    headers map[string]string,\n) (*api.InvokeResponse, error)\n\n// DeleteSession deletes a session\nfunc (h *AgentRuntimeHelper) DeleteSession(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    sessionID string,\n) error\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreter Helpers\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterHelper provides utilities for CodeInterpreter E2E tests\ntype CodeInterpreterHelper struct {\n    framework *TestFramework\n}\n\n// NewCodeInterpreterHelper creates a new CodeInterpreter helper\nfunc NewCodeInterpreterHelper(f *TestFramework) *CodeInterpreterHelper\n\n// CreateCodeInterpreter creates a CodeInterpreter resource\nfunc (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) CreateCodeInterpreter(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    ci *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter,\n) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n\n// GetCodeInterpreter retrieves a CodeInterpreter resource\nfunc (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) GetCodeInterpreter(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    name string,\n) (*v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter, error)\n\n// WaitForCodeInterpreterReady waits for CodeInterpreter to be ready\nfunc (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    name string,\n    timeout time.Duration,\n) error\n\n// ExecuteCode executes code in a CodeInterpreter session\nfunc (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) ExecuteCode(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    sessionID string,\n    code string,\n) (*api.ExecuteResponse, error)\n\n// UploadFile uploads a file to a CodeInterpreter session\nfunc (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) UploadFile(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    sessionID string,\n    filename string,\n    content []byte,\n) error\n\n// DownloadFile downloads a file from a CodeInterpreter session\nfunc (h *CodeInterpreterHelper) DownloadFile(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    sessionID string,\n    filename string,\n) ([]byte, error)\n```\n\n### Assertions\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/framework/assertions.go`\n\n```go\n// EventuallyWithTimeout provides Gomega's Eventually with custom timeout\nfunc EventuallyWithTimeout(\n    actual interface{},\n    timeout time.Duration,\n    intervals ...interface{},\n) AsyncAssertion\n\n// ConsistentlyWithTimeout provides Gomega's Consistently with custom timeout\nfunc ConsistentlyWithTimeout(\n    actual interface{},\n    timeout time.Duration,\n    intervals ...interface{},\n) AsyncAssertion\n\n// HaveConditions verifies conditions match\nfunc HaveConditions(expected ...metav1.Condition) OmegaMatcher\n\n// BeReady verifies resource is ready\nfunc BeReady() OmegaMatcher\n\n// HavePhase verifies resource phase\nfunc HavePhase(phase string) OmegaMatcher\n\n// HaveEndpoint verifies endpoint is accessible\nfunc HaveEndpoint(endpoint string) OmegaMatcher\n\n// ReturnSuccess verifies HTTP call succeeds\nfunc ReturnSuccess() OmegaMatcher\n\n// ReturnStatusCode verifies HTTP status code\nfunc ReturnStatusCode(code int) OmegaMatcher\n\n// HaveSessionID verifies response has session ID\nfunc HaveSessionID() OmegaMatcher\n```\n\n### Fixtures\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/framework/fixtures.go`\n\n```go\n// NewTestAgentRuntime creates a test AgentRuntime with defaults\nfunc NewTestAgentRuntime(name string) *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n\n// NewTestAgentRuntimeWithSpec creates a test AgentRuntime with custom spec\nfunc NewTestAgentRuntimeWithSpec(\n    name string,\n    spec v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec,\n) *v1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n\n// NewTestCodeInterpreter creates a test CodeInterpreter with defaults\nfunc NewTestCodeInterpreter(name string) *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n\n// NewTestCodeInterpreterWithSpec creates a test CodeInterpreter with custom spec\nfunc NewTestCodeInterpreterWithSpec(\n    name string,\n    spec v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec,\n) *v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n\n// NewTestSessionRequest creates a test session request\nfunc NewTestSessionRequest(kind, name, namespace string) *api.CreateSandboxRequest\n\n// NewTestInvokePayload creates a test invoke payload\nfunc NewTestInvokePayload(data map[string]interface{}) []byte\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### E2E Test Suite Structure\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/agentruntime_suite_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage e2e\n\nimport (\n    . \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n    . \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n    \n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/test/e2e/framework\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"AgentRuntime E2E\", func() {\n    var (\n        f       *framework.TestFramework\n        helper  *framework.AgentRuntimeHelper\n        ns      string\n    )\n\n    BeforeSuite(func() {\n        // Initialize framework\n        f = framework.NewDefaultFramework(\"agentruntime-e2e\")\n        \n        // Get or create namespace\n        ns = f.Namespace\n        \n        // Wait for AgentCube deployment to be ready\n        Eventually(func() bool {\n            return f.AgentCubeReady()\n        }, 5*time.Minute, 10*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n        \n        // Initialize helper\n        helper = framework.NewAgentRuntimeHelper(f)\n    })\n\n    AfterSuite(func() {\n        if !f.Options.SkipCleanup {\n            f.Cleanup()\n        }\n    })\n    \n    // Test contexts will be included here\n})\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Creation Tests\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/creation_test.go`\n\n```go\nvar _ = Context(\"AgentRuntime Creation\", func() {\n    It(\"should create AgentRuntime successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-creation\")\n        art.Namespace = ns\n        \n        // Create AgentRuntime\n        created, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        Expect(created.Name).To(Equal(art.Name))\n        Expect(created.Namespace).To(Equal(ns))\n    }, SpecTimeout(2*time.Minute))\n\n    It(\"should apply default values\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        art := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n            ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n                Name:      \"test-defaults\",\n                Namespace: ns,\n            },\n            Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n                PodTemplate: runtimev1alpha1.PodTemplateSpec{\n                    Spec: runtimev1alpha1.PodSpec{\n                        Containers: []runtimev1alpha1.Container{\n                            {\n                                Name:  \"agent\",\n                                Image: \"nginx:latest\",\n                            },\n                        },\n                    },\n                },\n            },\n        }\n        \n        created, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        // Verify defaults\n        Expect(created.Spec.MaxSessionDuration).To(Equal(\"8h\"))\n        Expect(created.Spec.SessionTimeout).To(Equal(\"15m\"))\n    }, SpecTimeout(2*time.Minute))\n\n    It(\"should become ready\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-ready\")\n        art.Namespace = ns\n        \n        _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        // Wait for ready status\n        err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        // Verify status\n        fetched, err := helper.GetAgentRuntime(ctx, art.Name)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        Expect(fetched.Status.Ready).To(BeTrue())\n    }, SpecTimeout(6*time.Minute))\n})\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Invocation Tests\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/invocation_test.go`\n\n```go\nvar _ = Context(\"AgentRuntime Invocation\", func() {\n    var (\n        art       *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n        sessionID string\n    )\n\n    BeforeEach(func() {\n        // Create AgentRuntime\n        art = framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-invocation\")\n        art.Namespace = ns\n        \n        ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 2*time.Minute)\n        defer cancel()\n        \n        var err error\n        art, err = helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        // Wait for ready\n        err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n    })\n\n    It(\"should create session successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n        \n        resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        Expect(resp).NotTo(BeNil())\n        Expect(resp.SessionID).NotTo(BeEmpty())\n        \n        sessionID = resp.SessionID\n    }, SpecTimeout(2*time.Minute))\n\n    It(\"should invoke session successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        // First create session\n        req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n        resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        sessionID = resp.SessionID\n        \n        // Invoke session\n        payload := framework.NewTestInvokePayload(map[string]interface{}{\n            \"message\": \"hello\",\n        })\n        \n        invokeResp, err := helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, payload, nil)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        Expect(invokeResp.StatusCode).To(Equal(200))\n    }, SpecTimeout(3*time.Minute))\n\n    It(\"should handle concurrent invocations\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        // Create session\n        req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n        resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        sessionID = resp.SessionID\n        \n        // Concurrent invocations\n        var wg sync.WaitGroup\n        errors := make(chan error, 10)\n        \n        for i := 0; i < 10; i++ {\n            wg.Add(1)\n            go func() {\n                defer wg.Done()\n                payload := framework.NewTestInvokePayload(map[string]interface{}{\n                    \"id\": i,\n                })\n                _, err := helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, payload, nil)\n                errors <- err\n            }()\n        }\n        \n        wg.Wait()\n        close(errors)\n        \n        // Verify all invocations succeeded\n        for err := range errors {\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        }\n    }, SpecTimeout(5*time.Minute))\n})\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Lifecycle Tests\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/agentruntime/lifecycle_test.go`\n\n```go\nvar _ = Context(\"AgentRuntime Lifecycle\", func() {\n    It(\"should handle session expiration\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        // Create AgentRuntime with short session timeout\n        art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-expiration\")\n        art.Namespace = ns\n        art.Spec.SessionTimeout = \"30s\"\n        \n        _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        // Create session\n        req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n        resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        sessionID := resp.SessionID\n        \n        // Wait for expiration\n        time.Sleep(35 * time.Second)\n        \n        // Verify session is expired\n        _, err = helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, []byte(\"{}\"), nil)\n        Expect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n    }, SpecTimeout(7*time.Minute))\n\n    It(\"should delete session successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n        art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(\"test-deletion\")\n        art.Namespace = ns\n        \n        _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        err = helper.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, art.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        // Create session\n        req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", art.Name, ns)\n        resp, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        sessionID := resp.SessionID\n        \n        // Delete session\n        err = helper.DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID)\n        Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n        \n        // Verify session is deleted\n        _, err = helper.InvokeSession(ctx, sessionID, []byte(\"{}\"), nil)\n        Expect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n    }, SpecTimeout(8*time.Minute))\n})\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreter Execution Tests\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/codeinterpreter/execution_test.go`\n\n```go\nvar _ = Describe(\"CodeInterpreter E2E\", func() {\n    var (\n        f       *framework.TestFramework\n        helper  *framework.CodeInterpreterHelper\n        ns      string\n    )\n\n    BeforeSuite(func() {\n        f = framework.NewDefaultFramework(\"codeinterpreter-e2e\")\n        ns = f.Namespace\n        \n        Eventually(func() bool {\n            return f.AgentCubeReady()\n        }, 5*time.Minute, 10*time.Second).Should(BeTrue())\n        \n        helper = framework.NewCodeInterpreterHelper(f)\n    })\n\n    AfterSuite(func() {\n        if !f.Options.SkipCleanup {\n            f.Cleanup()\n        }\n    })\n\n    Context(\"Code Execution\", func() {\n        It(\"should execute Python code successfully\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n            ci := framework.NewTestCodeInterpreter(\"test-execution\")\n            ci.Namespace = ns\n            \n            _, err := helper.CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx, ci)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n            \n            err = helper.WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(ctx, ci.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n            \n            // Create session and execute code\n            // (implementation depends on CodeInterpreter API)\n        }, SpecTimeout(6*time.Minute))\n\n        It(\"should handle syntax errors\", func(ctx SpecContext) {\n            ci := framework.NewTestCodeInterpreter(\"test-syntax-error\")\n            ci.Namespace = ns\n            \n            _, err := helper.CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx, ci)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n            \n            err = helper.WaitForCodeInterpreterReady(ctx, ci.Name, 5*time.Minute)\n            Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n            \n            // Execute code with syntax error\n            // Verify error is returned\n        }, SpecTimeout(6*time.Minute))\n    })\n})\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Test Failure Handling\n\n```go\n// TestFailureHandler provides error handling for test failures\ntype TestFailureHandler struct {\n    framework *TestFramework\n}\n\n// OnFailure handles test failures by collecting diagnostics\nfunc (h *TestFailureHandler) OnFailure(failedSpec SpecReport) {\n    // Collect pod logs\n    h.collectPodLogs(failedSpec)\n    \n    // Collect resource status\n    h.collectResourceStatus(failedSpec)\n    \n    // Collect events\n    h.collectEvents(failedSpec)\n    \n    // Save diagnostics to file\n    h.saveDiagnostics(failedSpec)\n}\n\nfunc (h *TestFailureHandler) collectPodLogs(spec SpecReport) {\n    pods, err := h.framework.Clientset.CoreV1().Pods(h.framework.Namespace).List(\n        context.Background(),\n        metav1.ListOptions{},\n    )\n    if err != nil {\n        return\n    }\n    \n    for _, pod := range pods.Items {\n        logFile := fmt.Sprintf(\"logs/%s-%s.log\", spec.LeafNodeText, pod.Name)\n        \n        for _, container := range pod.Spec.Containers {\n            logs, err := h.framework.Clientset.CoreV1().Pods(h.framework.Namespace).GetLogs(\n                pod.Name,\n                &corev1.PodLogOptions{\n                    Container: container.Name,\n                },\n            ).DoRaw(context.Background())\n            \n            if err == nil {\n                os.WriteFile(logFile, logs, 0644)\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Retry Logic\n\n```go\n// Retryable provides retry logic for flaky operations\nfunc Retryable(\n    fn func() error,\n    maxRetries int,\n    backoff time.Duration,\n) error {\n    var lastErr error\n    \n    for i := 0; i < maxRetries; i++ {\n        err := fn()\n        if err == nil {\n            return nil\n        }\n        \n        lastErr = err\n        time.Sleep(backoff * time.Duration(i+1))\n    }\n    \n    return lastErr\n}\n\n// EventuallyRetryable combines Gomega's Eventually with retry\nfunc EventuallyRetryable(\n    actual interface{},\n    timeout time.Duration,\n    pollingInterval time.Duration,\n    maxRetries int,\n) AsyncAssertion {\n    return Eventually(\n        actual,\n        timeout,\n        pollingInterval,\n    ).WithPolling(pollingInterval).WithTimeout(timeout)\n}\n```\n\n### Timeout Management\n\n```go\n// TimeoutContext creates a context with timeout and cancellation\nfunc TimeoutContext(timeout time.Duration) (context.Context, context.CancelFunc) {\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), timeout)\n    \n    // Handle timeout\n    go func() {\n        <-ctx.Done()\n        if ctx.Err() == context.DeadlineExceeded {\n            fmt.Printf(\"Operation timed out after %v\\n\", timeout)\n        }\n    }()\n    \n    return ctx, cancel\n}\n\n// WithDefaultTimeout creates a context with default test timeout\nfunc WithDefaultTimeout() (context.Context, context.CancelFunc) {\n    return TimeoutContext(5 * time.Minute)\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Execution Strategy\n\n#### Unit-Level E2E Tests\n\nTest individual components in an integrated environment:\n\n```go\n// Test AgentRuntime creation in isolation\nContext(\"AgentRuntime Creation\", func() {\n    It(\"should create AgentRuntime with valid spec\", func() {\n        // Test creation logic\n    })\n})\n```\n\n#### Workflow-Level E2E Tests\n\nTest complete workflows across multiple components:\n\n```go\n// Test complete pack -> build -> publish -> invoke workflow\nContext(\"Complete Workflow\", func() {\n    It(\"should execute pack -> build -> publish -> invoke workflow\", func() {\n        // Pack agent\n        // Build image\n        // Publish to cluster\n        // Invoke agent\n        // Verify results\n    })\n})\n```\n\n#### Integration-Level E2E Tests\n\nTest interactions between different components:\n\n```go\n// Test router -> workload-manager integration\nContext(\"Router Integration\", func() {\n    It(\"should route requests to workload-manager correctly\", func() {\n        // Create session via workload-manager\n        // Route request via router\n        // Verify routing\n    })\n})\n```\n\n### Test Parallelization\n\n```go\n// Run tests in parallel\nvar _ = Describe(\"Parallel Tests\", Ordered, func() {\n    BeforeAll(func() {\n        // Shared setup\n    })\n\n    Context(\"Test Group 1\", Serial, func() {\n        It(\"test 1\", func() {})\n        It(\"test 2\", func() {})\n    })\n\n    Context(\"Test Group 2\", Serial, func() {\n        It(\"test 3\", func() {})\n        It(\"test 4\", func() {})\n    })\n})\n```\n\n### Test Isolation\n\n```go\n// Each test gets its own namespace\nBeforeEach(func() {\n    ns = fmt.Sprintf(\"e2e-%s\", strings.ToLower(randomString(8)))\n    \n    _, err := f.Clientset.CoreV1().Namespaces().Create(\n        context.Background(),\n        &corev1.Namespace{\n            ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n                Name: ns,\n            },\n        },\n        metav1.CreateOptions{},\n    )\n    Expect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n})\n\nAfterEach(func() {\n    if !CurrentSpecReport().Failed() {\n        // Only cleanup on success to preserve state for debugging\n        f.Clientset.CoreV1().Namespaces().Delete(\n            context.Background(),\n            ns,\n            metav1.DeleteOptions{},\n        )\n    }\n})\n```\n\n### Test Data Management\n\n```go\n// TestData provides test data management\ntype TestData struct {\n    manifests map[string]string\n    configs   map[string]interface{}\n}\n\n// LoadManifests loads test manifests from files\nfunc (td *TestData) LoadManifests(dir string) error {\n    files, err := os.ReadDir(dir)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    for _, file := range files {\n        content, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, file.Name()))\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        \n        td.manifests[file.Name()] = string(content)\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n\n// GetManifest returns a specific manifest\nfunc (td *TestData) GetManifest(name string) string {\n    return td.manifests[name]\n}\n```\n\n### Test Reporting\n\n```go\n// TestReporter provides custom test reporting\ntype TestReporter struct {\n    outputPath string\n}\n\n// Report generates a test report\nfunc (r *TestReporter) Report(report types.Report) {\n    reportData := struct {\n        Summary  types.SuiteSummary\n        Specs    []types.SpecReport\n        Duration time.Duration\n    }{\n        Summary:  report.SuiteSummary,\n        Specs:    report.SpecReports,\n        Duration: report.EndTime.Sub(report.StartTime),\n    }\n    \n    // Generate HTML report\n    r.generateHTMLReport(reportData)\n    \n    // Generate JSON report\n    r.generateJSONReport(reportData)\n    \n    // Generate JUnit XML report\n    r.generateJUnitReport(reportData)\n}\n```\n\n## Environment Setup\n\n### Local Development Setup\n\n```bash\n# Create kind cluster\nkind create cluster --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Load Docker images\nkind load docker-image agentcube:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-workload-manager:latest --name agentcube-e2e\nkind load docker-image agentcube-router:latest --name agentcube-e2e\n\n# Deploy AgentCube\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/crds/\nkubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/\n\n# Wait for deployment\nkubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=5m \\\n    deployment/agentcube-controller-manager -n agentcube-system\n\n# Run E2E tests\ngo test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v\n```\n\n### CI/CD Integration\n\n```yaml\n# .github/workflows/e2e-tests.yml\nname: E2E Tests\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [main, develop]\n  pull_request:\n    branches: [main, develop]\n\njobs:\n  e2e-tests:\n    name: E2E Tests\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    \n    steps:\n      - name: Checkout code\n        uses: actions/checkout@v3\n      \n      - name: Set up Go\n        uses: actions/setup-go@v4\n        with:\n          go-version: '1.24'\n      \n      - name: Set up kind\n        uses: engineerd/setup-kind@v0.5.0\n        with:\n          version: v0.20.0\n          image: kindest/node:v1.28.0\n      \n      - name: Build images\n        run: |\n          make docker-build\n          kind load docker-image agentcube:latest\n      \n      - name: Deploy AgentCube\n        run: |\n          kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/crds/\n          kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/agentcube/\n          kubectl wait --for=condition=available --timeout=5m \\\n            deployment/agentcube-controller-manager -n agentcube-system\n      \n      - name: Run E2E tests\n        run: |\n          go test ./test/e2e/... -v -ginkgo.v -timeout 30m\n      \n      - name: Upload test results\n        if: always()\n        uses: actions/upload-artifact@v3\n        with:\n          name: e2e-test-results\n          path: test/e2e/reports/\n```\n\n### Test Manifests\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/manifests/agentruntimes/simple-agent.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: simple-agent\n  namespace: {{ .Namespace }}\nspec:\n  maxSessionDuration: \"1h\"\n  sessionTimeout: \"5m\"\n  targetPort:\n  - port: 8080\n    protocol: \"HTTP\"\n  podTemplate:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: agent\n        image: nginx:latest\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\n```\n\n**File**: `test/e2e/manifests/codeinterpreters/python-interpreter.yaml`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: CodeInterpreter\nmetadata:\n  name: python-interpreter\n  namespace: {{ .Namespace }}\nspec:\n  authMode: \"picod\"\n  maxSessionDuration: \"1h\"\n  sessionTimeout: \"5m\"\n  ports:\n  - port: 8080\n    protocol: \"HTTP\"\n  template:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - name: interpreter\n        image: python:3.11-slim\n```\n\n## Performance Testing\n\n### Load Testing\n\n```go\n// LoadTest performs load testing on the system\nfunc LoadTest(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    helper *framework.AgentRuntimeHelper,\n    agentName string,\n    concurrency int,\n    duration time.Duration,\n) error {\n    var wg sync.WaitGroup\n    errors := make(chan error, concurrency)\n    \n    done := make(chan struct{})\n    go func() {\n        time.Sleep(duration)\n        close(done)\n    }()\n    \n    for i := 0; i < concurrency; i++ {\n        wg.Add(1)\n        go func(id int) {\n            defer wg.Done()\n            \n            for {\n                select {\n                case <-done:\n                    return\n                default:\n                    req := framework.NewTestSessionRequest(\"AgentRuntime\", agentName, helper.Namespace())\n                    _, err := helper.CreateSession(ctx, req)\n                    errors <- err\n                }\n            }\n        }(i)\n    }\n    \n    wg.Wait()\n    close(errors)\n    \n    // Collect errors\n    var allErrors []error\n    for err := range errors {\n        if err != nil {\n            allErrors = append(allErrors, err)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if len(allErrors) > 0 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"load test failed with %d errors\", len(allErrors))\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Stress Testing\n\n```go\n// StressTest performs stress testing by creating many resources\nfunc StressTest(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    helper *framework.AgentRuntimeHelper,\n    count int,\n) error {\n    var wg sync.WaitGroup\n    errors := make(chan error, count)\n    \n    for i := 0; i < count; i++ {\n        wg.Add(1)\n        go func(id int) {\n            defer wg.Done()\n            \n            art := framework.NewTestAgentRuntime(fmt.Sprintf(\"stress-agent-%d\", id))\n            _, err := helper.CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, art)\n            errors <- err\n        }(i)\n    }\n    \n    wg.Wait()\n    close(errors)\n    \n    // Verify all creations succeeded\n    for err := range errors {\n        if err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation\n- [ ] Create test framework structure (`test/e2e/framework/`)\n- [ ] Implement `TestFramework` with environment setup\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeHelper` with CRUD operations\n- [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterHelper` with execution operations\n- [ ] Implement custom assertions\n- [ ] Create test fixtures\n\n### Phase 2: AgentRuntime Tests\n- [ ] Implement AgentRuntime creation tests\n- [ ] Implement AgentRuntime invocation tests\n- [ ] Implement AgentRuntime lifecycle tests\n- [ ] Implement AgentRuntime error handling tests\n- [ ] Implement AgentRuntime concurrent access tests\n\n### Phase 3: CodeInterpreter Tests\n- [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter creation tests\n- [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter execution tests\n- [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter file operations tests\n- [ ] Implement CodeInterpreter error handling tests\n\n### Phase 4: Integration Tests\n- [ ] Implement workflow tests (pack -> build -> publish -> invoke)\n- [ ] Implement routing integration tests\n- [ ] Implement session management tests\n- [ ] Implement scalability tests\n\n### Phase 5: Test Infrastructure\n- [ ] Implement test failure handler\n- [ ] Implement retry logic\n- [ ] Implement timeout management\n- [ ] Implement test reporting\n- [ ] Create test manifests\n\n### Phase 6: Documentation\n- [ ] Write test documentation\n- [ ] Create running tests guide\n- [ ] Document test patterns\n- [ ] Document CI/CD integration\n\n### Phase 7: Performance & Security\n- [ ] Implement load testing\n- [ ] Implement stress testing\n- [ ] Implement security testing\n- [ ] Create performance baselines\n\n## References\n\n- [Ginkgo Testing Framework](https://onsi.github.io/ginkgo/)\n- [Gomega Matchers Library](https://onsi.github.io/gomega/)\n- [kind (Kubernetes in Docker)](https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/)\n- [client-go Documentation](https://github.com/kubernetes/client-go)\n- [AgentCube Project](../../README.md)\n- [client-go Library](../../deployment/client-go.md)\n- [Workload Manager Design](../../pkg/workloadmanager/design-testing.md)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/test/e2e/design.md","time":{"start":1775896485545,"end":1775896485562}}}}
